Max, do step out of character for a moment and try and be charming.

774
01:08:12,292 --> 01:08:13,691
Well?

775
01:08:14,594 --> 01:08:15,788
Well what?

776
01:08:16,029 --> 01:08:18,930
Have you made up his mind? Do I hear wedding bells?

777
01:08:19,199 --> 01:08:21,190
- Pealing madly. - Marvelous.

778
01:08:21,434 --> 01:08:24,198
- Not necessarily for me. - What kind of talk's that?

779
01:08:24,404 --> 01:08:25,962
None-of-your-business talk.

780
01:08:26,272 --> 01:08:28,706
I'm terribly fond of him, so don't toy with us.

781
01:08:28,975 --> 01:08:32,570
But I'm a child. I like toys. So tell me everything.

782
01:08:32,879 --> 01:08:37,942
Come on. Tell me every teensy-weensy, intimate, disgusting detail.

783
01:08:39,419 --> 01:08:43,549
Well, let's just say I have a feeling I may be here on approval.

784
01:08:43,790 --> 01:08:46,816
- I approve of that. How can you miss? - Far too easily.

785
01:08:47,093 --> 01:08:50,324
If I know you, darling, and I do, you will find a way.

786
01:08:50,597 --> 01:08:53,088
- He's no ordinary man. - No, he's rich.

787
01:08:53,333 --> 01:08:55,597
His wife's death gave him a great heartache.

788
01:08:55,802 --> 01:08:58,930
And your husband's death gave you a great fortune.

789
01:08:59,138 --> 01:09:01,106
Oh, Max, you really are a beast.

790
01:09:01,307 --> 01:09:05,334
You and Georg are like family. That's why I want to see you married.

791
01:09:05,578 --> 01:09:09,139
We must keep all that lovely money in the family.

792
01:09:25,431 --> 01:09:28,366
- What are you doing there? - Oh, Captain von Trapp.

793
01:09:28,635 --> 01:09:30,660
I was just looking for...

794
01:09:31,537 --> 01:09:34,370
I didn't see, I mean, I didn't know you were...

795
01:09:34,974 --> 01:09:36,669
Heil Hitler!

796
01:09:37,377 --> 01:09:38,867
Who are you?

797
01:09:39,145 --> 01:09:41,375
I have a telegram for Herr Detweiler.

798
01:09:41,648 --> 01:09:44,378
- I am Herr Detweiler. - Yes, sir.

799
01:09:49,455 --> 01:09:52,049
You've delivered your telegram. Now get out.

800
01:09:58,831 --> 01:10:02,232
- Georg, he's just a boy. - Yes, and I'm just an Austrian.

801
01:10:02,468 --> 01:10:05,232
Things will happen. Make sure they don't happen to you.

802
01:10:05,538 --> 01:10:08,200
Max! Don't you ever say that again.

803
01:10:08,474 --> 01:10:10,669
I have no political convictions.

804
01:10:10,910 --> 01:10:13,845
- Can I help it if other people do? - You can help it.

805
01:10:14,981 --> 01:10:17,142
You must help it.

806
01:10:27,427 --> 01:10:29,019
Hello?

807
01:10:31,664 --> 01:10:34,428
You're far away. Where are you?

808
01:10:34,734 --> 01:10:38,602
In a world that's disappearing, I'm afraid.

809
01:10:39,439 --> 01:10:43,034
Is there any way I could bring you back to the world I'm in?

810
01:11:08,968 --> 01:11:11,459
- Father! Father! - There's your father!

811
01:11:12,271 --> 01:11:14,899
Oh, captain, you're home!

812
01:11:23,282 --> 01:11:25,944
Come out of that water at once!

813
01:11:35,061 --> 01:11:37,256
Oh, you must be Baroness Schraeder.

814
01:11:42,568 --> 01:11:45,560
I'm soaked to the skin!

815
01:11:57,517 --> 01:11:58,916
Straight line!

816
01:12:13,599 --> 01:12:15,999
This is Baroness Schraeder.

817
01:12:18,604 --> 01:12:20,367
And these...

818
01:12:20,606 --> 01:12:22,198
...are my children.

819
01:12:23,309 --> 01:12:24,799
How do you do?

820
01:12:25,878 --> 01:12:30,611
Go inside, dry off, clean up, change your clothes and report back here!

821
01:12:35,621 --> 01:12:37,714
Fraulein, you will stay here, please!

822
01:12:39,459 --> 01:12:43,020
I think I'd better go see what Max is up to.

823
01:12:53,239 --> 01:12:55,002
Now, fraulein...

824
01:12:56,909 --> 01:12:58,968
...I want a truthful answer.

825
01:12:59,378 --> 01:13:00,845
Yes, captain.

826
01:13:01,147 --> 01:13:05,208
Is it possible, or could I have just imagined it?

827
01:13:06,719 --> 01:13:11,213
Have my children, by any chance, been climbing trees today?

828
01:13:11,691 --> 01:13:12,851
Yes, captain.

829
01:13:13,926 --> 01:13:15,257
I see.

830
01:13:15,828 --> 01:13:20,322
And where, may I ask, did they get these...

831
01:13:20,600 --> 01:13:22,659
- Play clothes. - Is that what they are?

832
01:13:22,869 --> 01:13:26,270
I made them from the drapes that used to hang in my bedroom.

833
01:13:27,073 --> 01:13:29,200
- Drapes? - They have plenty of wear left.

834
01:13:29,408 --> 01:13:31,342
We've been everywhere in them.

835
01:13:31,577 --> 01:13:36,037
Are you telling me that my children have been roaming about Salzburg...

836
01:13:36,249 --> 01:13:39,616
...dressed up in nothing but some old drapes?

837
01:13:39,852 --> 01:13:41,513
And having a marvelous time!

838
01:13:41,721 --> 01:13:44,952
- They have uniforms. - Forgive me, straitjackets.

839
01:13:45,191 --> 01:13:47,955
They can't be children if they worry about clothes...

840
01:13:48,227 --> 01:13:49,353
They don't complain.

841
01:13:49,595 --> 01:13:52,291
They don't dare. They love you too much and fear...

842
01:13:52,532 --> 01:13:54,090
Don't discuss my children.

843
01:13:54,300 --> 01:13:56,234
You've got to hear, you're never home...

844
01:13:56,435 --> 01:13:57,959
I don't want to hear more!

845
01:13:58,204 --> 01:14:00,695
I know you don't, but you've got to!

846
01:14:01,474 --> 01:14:03,635
- Liesl's not a child. - Not one word...

847
01:14:03,910 --> 01:14:06,777
Soon she'll be a woman and you won't even know her.

848
01:14:07,046 --> 01:14:10,106
Friedrich wants to be a man but you're not here to show...

849
01:14:10,383 --> 01:14:11,714
Don't you dare tell me...

850
01:14:11,951 --> 01:14:15,216
Brigitta could tell you about him. She notices everything.

851
01:14:15,454 --> 01:14:18,582
Kurt acts tough to hide the pain when you ignore him...

852
01:14:18,791 --> 01:14:20,315
...the way you do all of them.

853
01:14:20,593 --> 01:14:22,993
Louisa, I don't know about yet.

854
01:14:23,262 --> 01:14:26,459
The little ones just want love. Please, love them all.

855
01:14:26,732 --> 01:14:28,256
I don't care to hear more.

856
01:14:28,501 --> 01:14:32,597
- I am not finished yet, captain! - Oh, yes, you are, captain!

857
01:14:34,140 --> 01:14:35,300
Fraulein.

858
01:14:36,609 --> 01:14:40,739
Now, you will pack your things this minute...

859
01:14:40,947 --> 01:14:43,438
...and return to the abbey.

860
01:14:46,085 --> 01:14:47,416
What's that?

861
01:14:49,155 --> 01:14:50,179
It's singing.

862
01:14:50,823 --> 01:14:53,621
Yes, I realize it's singing. But who is singing?

863
01:14:54,594 --> 01:14:56,152
The children.

864
01:14:59,031 --> 01:15:00,362
The children?

865
01:15:00,933 --> 01:15:03,663
I taught them something to sing for the baroness.

866
01:15:09,308 --> 01:15:15,338
My heart wants to sing Every song it hears

867
01:15:15,615 --> 01:15:18,175
Every song that it hears

868
01:15:18,451 --> 01:15:23,889
My heart wants to beat like the wings Of the birds that rise

869
01:15:24,156 --> 01:15:27,284
From the lake to the trees

870
01:15:27,526 --> 01:15:28,959
To the trees

871
01:15:29,195 --> 01:15:34,132
My heart wants to sigh Like a chime that flies

872
01:15:34,333 --> 01:15:38,963
From a church on a breeze

873
01:15:39,238 --> 01:15:43,140
To laugh like a brook When it trips and falls

874
01:15:43,409 --> 01:15:46,344
