875
01:15:46,646 --> 01:15:48,011
On its way

876
01:15:48,247 --> 01:15:52,684
To sing through the night

877
01:15:52,885 --> 01:15:58,551
Like a lark who is learning to pray

878
01:15:58,824 --> 01:16:03,318
I go to the hills

879
01:16:03,529 --> 01:16:09,764
When my heart is lonely

880
01:16:10,036 --> 01:16:13,733
I know I will hear

881
01:16:14,006 --> 01:16:19,774
What I've heard before

882
01:16:20,613 --> 01:16:24,845
My heart will be blessed

883
01:16:25,084 --> 01:16:32,047
With the sound of music

884
01:16:32,925 --> 01:16:38,124
And I'll sing...

885
01:16:38,364 --> 01:16:46,464
...once more

886
01:17:19,739 --> 01:17:21,502
Edelweiss!

887
01:17:25,478 --> 01:17:28,641
You never told me how enchanting your children are.

888
01:17:37,256 --> 01:17:38,814
Don't go away.

889
01:17:43,929 --> 01:17:45,328
Fraulein.

890
01:17:48,667 --> 01:17:49,861
I...

891
01:17:51,337 --> 01:17:54,135
...behaved badly. I apologize.

892
01:17:55,875 --> 01:17:59,470
I'm far too outspoken. It's one of my worst faults.

893
01:17:59,879 --> 01:18:01,346
You were right.

894
01:18:03,816 --> 01:18:05,716
I don't know my children.

895
01:18:07,019 --> 01:18:11,149
There's still time, captain. They want so much to be close to you.

896
01:18:11,490 --> 01:18:15,358
And you brought music back into the house.

897
01:18:16,695 --> 01:18:18,128
I'd forgotten.

898
01:18:20,866 --> 01:18:22,197
Fraulein.

899
01:18:24,703 --> 01:18:25,965
I want you to stay.

900
01:18:29,975 --> 01:18:32,705
I ask you to stay.

901
01:18:34,547 --> 01:18:38,039
- Lf I could be of any help. - You have already.

902
01:18:38,651 --> 01:18:39,709
More than you know.

903
01:18:59,438 --> 01:19:00,769
Marta.

904
01:19:01,507 --> 01:19:02,735
Curtain!

905
01:19:05,411 --> 01:19:08,744
High on a hill was a lonely goatherd

906
01:19:10,249 --> 01:19:13,514
Loud was the voice Of the lonely goatherd

907
01:19:15,020 --> 01:19:18,285
Folks in a town That was quite remote heard

908
01:19:19,859 --> 01:19:23,090
Lusty and clear From the goatherd's throat heard

909
01:19:34,607 --> 01:19:37,474
Marta. Marta!

910
01:19:39,879 --> 01:19:41,870
Gretl, the prince!

911
01:19:43,616 --> 01:19:47,074
A prince on the bridge Of a castle moat heard

912
01:19:48,554 --> 01:19:50,886
Men on a road With a load to tote heard

913
01:19:53,392 --> 01:19:56,657
Men in the midst Of a table d'hote heard

914
01:19:57,997 --> 01:20:01,262
Men drinking beer With the foam afloat heard

915
01:20:12,344 --> 01:20:15,472
One little girl In a pale pink coat heard

916
01:20:17,116 --> 01:20:20,449
She yodeled back To the lonely goatherd

917
01:20:21,620 --> 01:20:25,021
Soon her mama With a gleaming gloat heard

918
01:20:26,525 --> 01:20:29,824
What a duet for a girl and goatherd

919
01:21:16,408 --> 01:21:19,673
One little girl In a pale pink coat heard

920
01:21:21,213 --> 01:21:24,478
