- Small and white - Small and white

989
01:26:27,986 --> 01:26:31,444
- Clean and bright - Clean and bright

990
01:26:31,657 --> 01:26:34,148
You look happy...

991
01:26:34,393 --> 01:26:38,022
...to meet me

992
01:26:38,497 --> 01:26:40,624
Blossom of snow

993
01:26:40,832 --> 01:26:44,996
May you bloom and grow

994
01:26:45,237 --> 01:26:52,302
Bloom and grow forever

995
01:26:52,544 --> 01:26:56,173
Edelweiss

996
01:26:56,415 --> 01:26:59,077
Edelweiss

997
01:26:59,685 --> 01:27:09,583
Bless my homeland forever

998
01:27:18,870 --> 01:27:22,533
Anytime you say the word, Georg, you can be part of my new act:

999
01:27:22,741 --> 01:27:25,232
The von Trapp Family Singers.

1000
01:27:26,345 --> 01:27:28,836
I have a wonderful idea, Georg.

1001
01:27:29,081 --> 01:27:31,549
Let's really fill this house with music.

1002
01:27:31,783 --> 01:27:34,752
You must give a grand and glorious party for me.

1003
01:27:35,020 --> 01:27:37,716
- A party? - Yes, Father, please!

1004
01:27:37,923 --> 01:27:40,289
It's high time I met all your friends...

1005
01:27:40,592 --> 01:27:43,083
...and they met me. Don't you agree?

1006
01:27:43,362 --> 01:27:45,592
- I see what you mean. - Oh, please!

1007
01:27:45,864 --> 01:27:49,027
Children, it's bedtime. Come now, say good night.

1008
01:27:49,968 --> 01:27:51,265
Good night, Father.

1009
01:27:51,470 --> 01:27:54,303
- Good night. - Good night, Baroness Schraeder.

1010
01:27:54,539 --> 01:27:56,097
Good night, Father.

1011
01:27:59,077 --> 01:28:00,908
Good night, Uncle Max.

1012
01:28:02,814 --> 01:28:05,977
It'll be my first party, Father!

1013
01:28:38,517 --> 01:28:41,145
- Captain. - Herr Zeller. Baroness Schraeder.

1014
01:28:41,353 --> 01:28:44,481
- Good evening, Herr Zeller. - Baroness.

1015
01:28:45,791 --> 01:28:48,259
How do you do? Good evening.

1016
01:29:08,880 --> 01:29:12,316
Did you notice the obvious display of the Austrian flag?

1017
01:29:19,391 --> 01:29:21,188
The women look so beautiful.

1018
01:29:21,460 --> 01:29:22,791
I think they look ugly.

1019
01:29:23,061 --> 01:29:24,892
You're just scared of them.

1020
01:29:25,130 --> 01:29:27,360
Silly, only grown-up men fear women.

1021
01:29:27,966 --> 01:29:31,527
- I think the men look beautiful. - How would you know?

1022
01:29:49,172 --> 01:29:51,197
Liesl, who are you dancing with?

1023
01:29:51,408 --> 01:29:53,035
Nobody.

1024
01:29:53,844 --> 01:29:55,744
Oh, yes, you are.

1025
01:29:58,215 --> 01:29:59,705
May I have this dance?

1026
01:29:59,916 --> 01:30:02,407
I'd be delighted, young man.

1027
01:30:09,192 --> 01:30:11,854
Why didn't you tell me you could dance?

1028
01:30:12,095 --> 01:30:17,032
We feared you'd make us all dance. The von Trapp Family Dancers.

1029
01:30:21,438 --> 01:30:23,133
What are they playing?

1030
01:30:23,373 --> 01:30:26,001
It's the Laendler. An Austrian folk dance.

1031
01:30:26,209 --> 01:30:29,372
- Show me. - I haven't danced since I was little.

1032
01:30:29,579 --> 01:30:31,547
You remember. Please?

1033
01:30:31,815 --> 01:30:33,749
- Well... - Please.

1034
01:30:33,984 --> 01:30:36,214
All right. Come on over here.

1035
01:30:36,720 --> 01:30:39,553
Now you bow and I curtsy.

1036
01:30:40,490 --> 01:30:43,425
- Like this? - Fine. Now we go for a little walk.

1037
01:30:43,660 --> 01:30:46,322
One, two, three. One, two, three.

1038
01:30:46,630 --> 01:30:51,226
One, two, three, step together. Now, step hop, step hop.

1039
01:30:51,468 --> 01:30:54,130
Now turn under. Not quite.

1040
01:30:54,337 --> 01:30:58,296
This way. Hop step, hop. And under.

1041
01:30:58,975 --> 01:31:00,670
Kurt, we'll have to practice.

1042
01:31:00,911 --> 01:31:02,401
Do allow me, will you?

1043
01:32:30,700 --> 01:32:32,565
I don't remember anymore.

1044
01:32:34,738 --> 01:32:36,933
- Your face is all red. - Is it?

1045
01:32:38,274 --> 01:32:40,367
I don't suppose I'm used to dancing.

1046
01:32:43,079 --> 01:32:45,070
Why, that was beautifully done.

1047
01:32:45,348 --> 01:32:47,248
What a lovely couple you make.

1048
01:32:47,450 --> 01:32:49,577
It's time the children said good night.

1049
01:32:49,853 --> 01:32:51,184
We'll be in the hall.

1050
01:32:51,421 --> 01:32:54,288
- We have something special prepared. - Right!

1051
01:32:54,591 --> 01:32:55,751
Yes, come on!

1052
01:33:02,599 --> 01:33:04,931
All that needless worrying, Georg.

1053
01:33:05,201 --> 01:33:08,227
You thought you wouldn't find a friend at the party.

1054
01:33:11,141 --> 01:33:14,736
- A bit chilly out tonight, isn't it? - Oh, I don't know.

1055
01:33:14,944 --> 01:33:16,969
It seemed rather warm to me.

1056
01:33:21,151 --> 01:33:22,379
Ladies and gentlemen.

1057
01:33:23,119 --> 01:33:27,215
The children of Captain von Trapp wish to say good night to you.

1058
01:33:41,337 --> 01:33:45,239
There's a sad sort of clanging From the clock in the hall

1059
01:33:45,442 --> 01:33:49,173
And the bells in the steeple too

1060
01:33:49,446 --> 01:33:53,473
And up in the nursery An absurd little bird

1061
01:33:53,683 --> 01:33:56,117
Is popping up to say "coo-coo"

1062
01:33:56,352 --> 01:33:58,013
Coo-coo

1063
01:33:58,288 --> 01:33:59,516
Coo-coo

1064
01:33:59,756 --> 01:34:01,917
Regretfully they tell us

1065
01:34:02,125 --> 01:34:03,490
But firmly they compel us

1066
01:34:03,760 --> 01:34:06,820
To say goodbye

1067
01:34:07,030 --> 01:34:12,332
To you

1068
01:34:15,538 --> 01:34:19,440
So long, farewell Auf Wiedersehen, good night

1069
01:34:19,642 --> 01:34:23,510
I hate to go And leave this pretty sight

1070
01:34:30,787 --> 01:34:34,120
So long, farewell, Auf Wiedersehen, adieu

1071
01:34:34,791 --> 01:34:38,318
Adieu, adieu To you and you and you

1072
01:34:45,668 --> 01:34:49,468
So long, farewell Au revoir, auf Wiedersehen

1073
01:34:49,739 --> 01:34:53,675
I'd like to stay And taste my first champagne

1074
01:34:53,910 --> 01:34:56,344
- Yes? - No.

1075
01:35:00,683 --> 01:35:04,346
So long, farewell Auf Wiedersehen, goodbye

1076
01:35:04,687 --> 01:35:08,646
I leave and heave a sigh And say goodbye

1077
01:35:08,858 --> 01:35:12,851
Goodbye

1078
01:35:15,899 --> 01:35:18,993
I'm glad to go

1079
01:35:19,235 --> 01:35:22,102
I cannot tell a lie

1080
01:35:22,438 --> 01:35:25,430
I flit, I float

1081
01:35:25,708 --> 01:35:29,166
I fleetly flee, I fly

1082
01:35:39,222 --> 01:35:44,956
The sun has gone to bed

1083
01:35:45,195 --> 01:35:48,926
And so must I

1084
01:35:49,132 --> 01:35:51,532
So long

1085
01:35:51,768 --> 01:35:54,328
Farewell

1086
01:35:54,537 --> 01:35:59,941
Auf Wiedersehen, goodbye

1087
01:36:00,210 --> 01:36:05,546
Goodbye

1088
01:36:06,249 --> 01:36:11,812
Goodbye

1089
01:36:12,055 --> 01:36:18,927
Goodbye

1090
01:36:19,128 --> 01:36:27,627
Goodbye

1091
01:36:32,642 --> 01:36:35,406
Extraordinary! What they'd do at the festival.

1092
01:36:35,645 --> 01:36:38,136
Young lady, I must have a word with you.

1093
01:36:39,148 --> 01:36:43,141
Georg, you won't let this girl get away. She must join the party.

1094
01:36:43,419 --> 01:36:45,819
- No, really l... - Stop. Stop it now.

1095
01:36:46,089 --> 01:36:49,024
- Georg, please. - You can if you want to, fraulein.

1096
01:36:49,259 --> 01:36:51,750
I insist. You will be my dinner partner.

1097
01:36:51,961 --> 01:36:53,861
This is business. Franz...

1098
01:36:54,130 --> 01:36:57,293
...set another place next to mine for Fraulein Maria.

1099
01:36:59,469 --> 01:37:02,199
- Whatever you say. - It appears to be all arranged.

1100
01:37:03,006 --> 01:37:04,871
- It does. - I'm not suitably dressed.

1101
01:37:05,942 --> 01:37:07,432
You can change. We'll wait.

1102
01:37:11,047 --> 01:37:13,982
Captain, you must be very proud of your youngsters.

1103
01:37:14,183 --> 01:37:15,047
I am, thank you.

1104
01:37:15,318 --> 01:37:19,880
Is there a more beautiful expression of what is good in our country...

1105
01:37:20,123 --> 01:37:23,559
...than the innocent voices of our children?

1106
01:37:23,960 --> 01:37:25,325
Oh, come now, baron.

1107
01:37:25,561 --> 01:37:29,327
Would you have us believe that Austria holds a monopoly on virtue?

1108
01:37:30,233 --> 01:37:34,363
Herr Zeller, some of us prefer Austrian voices raised in song...

1109
01:37:34,570 --> 01:37:36,970
...to ugly German threats.

1110
01:37:38,041 --> 01:37:41,670
The ostrich buries his head in the sand...

1111
01:37:41,878 --> 01:37:44,813
...and sometimes in the flag.

1112
01:37:45,348 --> 01:37:49,546
Perhaps those who would warn you that the Anschluss is coming, and it is...

1113
01:37:49,819 --> 01:37:53,516
...would get further with you by setting their words to music.

1114
01:37:53,723 --> 01:37:58,387
If the Nazis take over Austria, you will be the entire trumpet section.

1115
01:37:58,695 --> 01:37:59,719
You flatter me.

1116
01:38:00,763 --> 01:38:04,665
Oh, how clumsy of me. I meant to accuse you.

1117
01:38:12,408 --> 01:38:14,899
It's very kind of you to offer to help me, baroness.

1118
01:38:15,178 --> 01:38:16,736
I'm delighted, Maria.

1119
01:38:17,213 --> 01:38:20,910
I really don't think I have anything that would be appropriate.

1120
01:38:21,384 --> 01:38:25,514
Now where is that lovely little thing you were wearing the other evening?

1121
01:38:25,755 --> 01:38:29,054
When the captain couldn't keep his eyes off you.

1122
01:38:32,428 --> 01:38:34,259
Couldn't keep his eyes off me?

1123
01:38:35,598 --> 01:38:37,395
Come, my dear, we are women.

1124
01:38:37,633 --> 01:38:41,034
Let's not pretend we don't know when a man notices us.

1125
01:38:41,270 --> 01:38:44,706
- Here we are. - The captain notices everybody.

1126
01:38:45,274 --> 01:38:47,708
There's no need to feel so defensive, Maria.

1127
01:38:47,944 --> 01:38:50,412
You are quite attractive, you know.

1128
01:38:50,646 --> 01:38:54,275
The captain would hardly be a man if he didn't notice you.

1129
01:38:55,885 --> 01:38:58,251
Baroness, I hope you're joking.

1130
01:38:58,721 --> 01:38:59,983
Not at all.

1131
01:39:00,223 --> 01:39:01,815
I've never done a thing to...

1132
01:39:02,091 --> 01:39:03,649
You don't have to, my dear.

1133
01:39:04,293 --> 01:39:09,128
Nothing's more irresistible to a man than a woman who's in love with him.

1134
01:39:10,400 --> 01:39:12,834
- In love with him? - Of course.

1135
01:39:13,770 --> 01:39:17,171
What makes it so nice is he thinks he's in love with you.

1136
01:39:19,909 --> 01:39:21,501
But that's not true.

1137
01:39:21,911 --> 01:39:25,403
Surely you've noticed the way he looks into your eyes.

1138
01:39:25,681 --> 01:39:30,584
And you know, you blushed in his arms when you were dancing just now.

1139
01:39:31,821 --> 01:39:33,516
Don't take it to heart.

1140
01:39:33,790 --> 01:39:36,088
He'll get over it soon enough, I think.

1141
01:39:36,359 --> 01:39:38,327
Men do, you know.

1142
01:39:39,328 --> 01:39:40,420
Then I should go.

1143
01:39:41,764 --> 01:39:43,197
I mustn't stay here.

1144
01:39:53,676 --> 01:39:57,112
- Is there something I can do to help? - No, nothing.

1145
01:39:58,881 --> 01:40:00,109
Yes.

1146
01:40:01,117 --> 01:40:03,142
Don't say a word to the captain.

1147
01:40:04,787 --> 01:40:08,348
No, I wouldn't dream of it.

1148
01:40:15,131 --> 01:40:16,689
Goodbye, Maria.

1149
01:40:17,500 --> 01:40:20,298
I'm sure you'll make a very fine nun.

1150
01:40:50,333 --> 01:40:52,324
Champagne, darling.

1151
01:40:52,735 --> 01:40:56,728
I feel like celebrating. Cheers.

1152
01:41:02,211 --> 01:41:05,112
- You know something. - Perhaps.

1153
01:41:05,348 --> 01:41:09,876
If you're so clever, tell me how to get fraulein to influence Georg.

1154
01:41:10,119 --> 01:41:12,747
I want those children in the festival.

1155
01:41:13,222 --> 01:41:15,520
Elsa, this is important to Austria.

1156
01:41:15,725 --> 01:41:17,420
Wouldn't do you any harm either.

1157
01:41:17,627 --> 01:41:19,219
I thought of that.

1158
01:41:19,462 --> 01:41:21,930
Well, if it's a matter of influence...

1159
01:41:22,131 --> 01:41:25,032
...maybe the one you have to be talking to is me.

1160
01:44:51,965 --> 01:44:54,195
- Two. - Three.

1161
01:44:54,467 --> 01:44:55,957
- Four. - Five.

1162
01:44:57,203 --> 01:44:59,228
- Six. - Seven.

1163
01:44:59,505 --> 01:45:01,132
Eight.

1164
01:45:01,374 --> 01:45:03,205
- Four. - Two.

1165
01:45:04,310 --> 01:45:06,141
- Seven. - Five.

1166
01:45:06,379 --> 01:45:08,574
- Two. - Six.

1167
01:45:13,219 --> 01:45:15,244
Isn't this fun?

1168
01:45:16,656 --> 01:45:18,988
- Four. - I'm number five.

1169
01:45:19,258 --> 01:45:21,419
- Oh, yes. - Eight.

1170
01:45:21,728 --> 01:45:24,094
- Two. - Four.

1171
01:45:24,497 --> 01:45:25,725
Six.

1172
01:45:28,201 --> 01:45:29,429
Two.

1173
01:45:30,570 --> 01:45:33,539
Baroness Schraeder, do you mind if we stop now? We're tired.

1174
01:45:33,773 --> 01:45:35,741
Whatever you want, dear.

1175
01:45:36,009 --> 01:45:38,000
We'll do it again tomorrow.

1176
01:45:48,187 --> 01:45:50,348
The country's so restful, isn't it?

1177
01:45:51,391 --> 01:45:53,018
Have some lemonade.

1178
01:45:54,260 --> 01:45:55,693
There must be an easier way.

1179
01:45:57,096 --> 01:46:00,361
I get a fiendish delight thinking of you as the mother of seven.

1180
01:46:01,300 --> 01:46:03,131
How do you plan to do it?

1181
01:46:03,403 --> 01:46:05,428
Darling, haven't you ever heard...

1182
01:46:05,705 --> 01:46:08,799
...of a delightful little thing called boarding school?

1183
01:46:09,942 --> 01:46:12,206
Baroness Machiavelli.

1184
01:46:13,546 --> 01:46:15,537
Uncle Max, where's Father?

1185
01:46:15,815 --> 01:46:17,612
I think he's in the house.

1186
01:46:17,817 --> 01:46:20,377
What's the matter with all you gloomy pussies?

1187
01:46:20,620 --> 01:46:23,418
- Nothing. - I know. Let's have a rehearsal.

1188
01:46:23,623 --> 01:46:24,521
What for?

1189
01:46:24,724 --> 01:46:27,215
Let's make believe we're on-stage at the festival.

1190
01:46:27,427 --> 01:46:31,295
- I don't feel like singing. - Not without Fraulein Maria.

1191
01:46:31,564 --> 01:46:33,964
Liesl, get the guitar. Come on, Marta.

1192
01:46:34,167 --> 01:46:37,136
Everybody into the group. Get in your places.

1193
01:46:37,403 --> 01:46:40,167
Now be cheerful, right? Give us the key, Liesl.

1194
01:46:42,075 --> 01:46:44,737
Now, impress me.

1195
01:46:48,748 --> 01:46:50,079
Gretl, why don't you sing?

1196
01:46:50,349 --> 01:46:52,817
I can't. I've got a sore finger.

1197
01:46:53,853 --> 01:46:56,913
But you sang so beautifully the night of the party.

1198
01:46:57,123 --> 01:46:59,455
Come on, all of you. Try something you know.

1199
01:46:59,692 --> 01:47:01,182
Enjoy it. Be cheerful.

1200
01:47:01,461 --> 01:47:03,088
All right, Liesl.

1201
01:47:05,031 --> 01:47:10,435
The hills are alive

1202
01:47:10,670 --> 01:47:18,338
With the sound of music

1203
01:47:19,545 --> 01:47:24,608
With songs they have sung

1204
01:47:24,851 --> 01:47:32,690
For a thousand years

1205
01:47:33,392 --> 01:47:38,796
The hills fill my heart

1206
01:47:39,031 --> 01:47:46,733
With the sound of music

1207
01:47:47,073 --> 01:47:49,701
They wanted to sing for me, bless their hearts.

1208
01:47:50,009 --> 01:47:51,909
That's lovely, lovely. Don't stop.

1209
01:47:55,915 --> 01:47:59,817
- Something long and cool, Georg? - No, thank you, darling.

1210
01:48:00,219 --> 01:48:02,653
- Father? - Yes, Brigitta?

1211
01:48:03,089 --> 01:48:05,353
Is it true Fraulein Maria isn't coming back?

1212
01:48:05,658 --> 01:48:08,752
Yes, I suppose it's true. What have we got here?

1213
01:48:09,061 --> 01:48:13,760
- Pink lemonade. - Laced with lemonade.

1214
01:48:14,500 --> 01:48:16,024
I don't believe it, Father.

1215
01:48:17,403 --> 01:48:19,428
- What? - About Fraulein Maria.

1216
01:48:19,839 --> 01:48:21,067
Oh, Fraulein Maria!

1217
01:48:21,374 --> 01:48:24,832
Didn't I tell you what her note said? I'm sure I did.

1218
01:48:25,578 --> 01:48:28,069
She said she missed her life at the abbey.

1219
01:48:28,347 --> 01:48:30,508
She had to leave us.

1220
01:48:30,750 --> 01:48:32,342
And that's all there is to it.

1221
01:48:34,053 --> 01:48:36,749
I think I'm brave enough to try some of that.

1222
01:48:36,956 --> 01:48:39,686
- She didn't even say goodbye. - She did in her note.

1223
01:48:39,959 --> 01:48:41,756
That isn't the same thing.

1224
01:48:42,061 --> 01:48:43,688
Not too sweet, not too sour.

1225
01:48:44,430 --> 01:48:46,421
Just too pink.

1226
01:48:47,867 --> 01:48:50,961
Father, who is our new governess going to be?

1227
01:48:57,610 --> 01:48:58,702
Well...

1228
01:49:01,047 --> 01:49:06,280
...you're not going to have a governess anymore.

1229
01:49:06,619 --> 01:49:09,281
- We're not? - No.

1230
01:49:11,490 --> 01:49:13,617
You're going to have a new mother.

1231
01:49:14,727 --> 01:49:16,752
A new mother?

1232
01:49:17,597 --> 01:49:20,725
We talked about it last night. It's all settled.

1233
01:49:20,933 --> 01:49:23,629
And we're all going to be very happy.

1234
01:49:56,636 --> 01:49:59,104
Well, all right, all right. Run off and play.

1235
01:50:31,070 --> 01:50:32,037
Yes, my children?

1236
01:50:32,238 --> 01:50:34,638
- My name is Liesl. - Yes, Liesl?

1237
01:50:35,141 --> 01:50:39,077
We, my brothers and sisters, want to see Fraulein Maria.

1238
01:50:40,246 --> 01:50:42,237
Fraulein Maria?

1239
01:50:43,015 --> 01:50:44,983
Oh, Maria.

1240
01:50:46,886 --> 01:50:48,717
Come in, please.

1241
01:50:52,591 --> 01:50:54,149
Wait here.

1242
01:51:05,104 --> 01:51:08,267
I'm Sister Margaretta. I understand you inquired about Maria.

1243
01:51:08,541 --> 01:51:11,032
We have to see her. Will you tell her we're here?

1244
01:51:11,277 --> 01:51:13,871
- I'm afraid I can't do that. - But you've got to!

1245
01:51:14,180 --> 01:51:16,239
- She's our governess. - We want her back.

1246
01:51:16,449 --> 01:51:18,349
She didn't even say goodbye.

1247
01:51:18,584 --> 01:51:20,347
All we want to do is talk to her.

1248
01:51:21,120 --> 01:51:24,021
I'm very sorry, but Maria is in seclusion.

1249
01:51:24,256 --> 01:51:27,350
- She hasn't been seeing anyone. - She'll see us.

1250
01:51:27,593 --> 01:51:30,084
I want to show her my finger.

1251
01:51:30,296 --> 01:51:32,196
Some other time, dear.

1252
01:51:32,465 --> 01:51:33,762
I'll tell her you were here.

1253
01:51:34,033 --> 01:51:37,093
- It was sweet of you to call. - We have to speak to her!

1254
01:51:37,737 --> 01:51:40,865
Run along, children. Run along home.

1255
01:51:41,073 --> 01:51:42,700
I'm sure she'd like to see us.

1256
01:51:42,975 --> 01:51:45,239
Sister Margaretta, please.

1257
01:51:45,478 --> 01:51:49,209
- Goodbye, children. - Sister Margaretta, may we, please?

1258
01:51:51,984 --> 01:51:53,713
What was that about, Sister?

1259
01:51:53,953 --> 01:51:56,148
The von Trapp children, Reverend Mother.

1260
01:51:56,389 --> 01:51:58,823
They want to see Maria.

1261
01:51:59,091 --> 01:52:01,389
Has she spoken yet? Has she told you anything?

1262
01:52:01,660 --> 01:52:05,653
She doesn't say a word, Reverend Mother, except in prayer.

1263
01:52:05,931 --> 01:52:06,920
Poor child.

1264
01:52:07,133 --> 01:52:10,102
It's strange. She seems happy to be back here...

1265
01:52:10,336 --> 01:52:13,635
...and yet she's unhappy too.

1266
01:52:14,907 --> 01:52:17,967
Perhaps I have been wrong in leaving her alone so long.

1267
01:52:18,244 --> 01:52:20,940
Bring her to me, even if she's not yet ready.

1268
01:52:21,147 --> 01:52:22,808
Yes, Reverend Mother.

1269
01:52:28,320 --> 01:52:31,812
Sister Augusta, take our new postulant to the robing room.

1270
01:52:32,825 --> 01:52:35,089
God bless you, my daughter.

1271
01:52:41,300 --> 01:52:43,029
Yes, bring her in.

1272
01:52:52,044 --> 01:52:54,308
You've been unhappy. I'm sorry.

1273
01:52:56,348 --> 01:52:57,542
Reverend Mother.

1274
01:52:57,883 --> 01:53:00,511
Why did they send you back to us?

1275
01:53:01,353 --> 01:53:03,321
They didn't send me back. I left.

1276
01:53:05,825 --> 01:53:07,383
Sit down, Maria.

1277
01:53:07,893 --> 01:53:09,690
Tell me what happened.

1278
01:53:14,900 --> 01:53:16,231
I was frightened.

1279
01:53:16,502 --> 01:53:20,962
- Frightened? Were they unkind to you. - Oh, no!

1280
01:53:21,207 --> 01:53:24,904
No, I was confused. I felt...

1281
01:53:26,378 --> 01:53:28,471
I've never felt that way before.

1282
01:53:28,714 --> 01:53:32,480
I couldn't stay. I knew that here I'd be away from it. I'd be safe.

1283
01:53:32,718 --> 01:53:37,417
Maria, our abbey is not to be used as an escape.

1284
01:53:37,690 --> 01:53:39,920
What is it you can't face?

1285
01:53:41,894 --> 01:53:43,327
I can't face him again.

1286
01:53:44,163 --> 01:53:45,687
Him?

1287
01:53:47,266 --> 01:53:49,325
Thank you, Sister Margaretta.

1288
01:53:58,944 --> 01:54:00,571
Captain von Trapp?

1289
01:54:06,018 --> 01:54:08,714
- Are you in love with him? - I don't know!

1290
01:54:08,954 --> 01:54:10,421
I don't know. L...

1291
01:54:10,956 --> 01:54:14,790
The baroness said I was. She said that he was in love with me.

1292
01:54:15,060 --> 01:54:17,722
But I didn't want to believe it.

1293
01:54:18,797 --> 01:54:21,095
There were times we looked at each other.

1294
01:54:21,300 --> 01:54:22,858
I could hardly breathe.

1295
01:54:23,235 --> 01:54:25,931
- Did you let him see your feelings? - I don't know.

1296
01:54:26,539 --> 01:54:29,201
That's what's torturing me. I was on God's errand.

1297
01:54:29,408 --> 01:54:34,402
To have asked for his love would have been wrong. I just couldn't stay.

1298
01:54:36,582 --> 01:54:39,380
I'm ready at this moment to take my vows.

1299
01:54:40,252 --> 01:54:43,312
- Please help me. - Maria.

1300
01:54:44,890 --> 01:54:49,589
The love of a man and a woman is holy. You have a great capacity to love.

1301
01:54:49,828 --> 01:54:52,763
You must find out how God wants you to spend your love.

1302
01:54:53,065 --> 01:54:56,899
But I pledged my life to God. I pledged my life to his service.

1303
01:54:57,102 --> 01:55:01,471
My daughter, if you love this man, it doesn't mean you love God less.

1304
01:55:03,142 --> 01:55:05,007
No.

1305
01:55:05,244 --> 01:55:07,109
You must find out.

1306
01:55:08,847 --> 01:55:11,338
You must go back.

1307
01:55:11,617 --> 01:55:13,585
You can't ask me to do that.

1308
01:55:13,786 --> 01:55:16,277
- Please let me stay. I beg... - Maria.

1309
01:55:16,488 --> 01:55:20,447
These walls were not built to shut out problems.

1310
01:55:20,659 --> 01:55:22,251
You have to face them.

1311
01:55:22,828 --> 01:55:26,093
You have to live the life you were born to live.

1312
01:55:31,971 --> 01:55:36,271
Climb every mountain

1313
01:55:36,508 --> 01:55:40,274
Search high and low

1314
01:55:40,512 --> 01:55:45,279
Follow every byway

1315
01:55:45,517 --> 01:55:49,783
Every path you know

1316
01:55:50,222 --> 01:55:54,682
Climb every mountain

1317
01:55:54,960 --> 01:55:59,294
Ford every stream

1318
01:55:59,531 --> 01:56:03,900
Follow every rainbow

1319
01:56:04,169 --> 01:56:08,503
Till you find your dream

1320
01:56:08,707 --> 01:56:11,801
A dream that will need

1321
01:56:12,044 --> 01:56:16,879
All the love you can give

1322
01:56:17,650 --> 01:56:21,051
Every day of your life

1323
01:56:21,320 --> 01:56:27,725
For as long as you live

1324
01:56:28,027 --> 01:56:32,327
Climb every mountain

1325
01:56:32,564 --> 01:56:36,898
Ford every stream

1326
01:56:37,169 --> 01:56:41,731
Follow every rainbow

1327
01:56:41,940 --> 01:56:50,348
Till you find your dream

1328
01:56:51,450 --> 01:56:54,942
A dream that will need

1329
01:56:55,254 --> 01:57:00,783
All the love you can give

1330
01:57:01,060 --> 01:57:04,552
Every day of your life

1331
01:57:04,797 --> 01:57:11,225
For as long as you live

1332
01:57:11,470 --> 01:57:15,907
Climb every mountain

1333
01:57:16,141 --> 01:57:20,077
Ford every stream

1334
01:57:20,746 --> 01:57:25,376
Follow every rainbow

1335
01:57:25,784 --> 01:57:29,880
Till you find...

1336
01:57:30,122 --> 01:57:40,123
...your dream

1337
01:57:42,668 --> 01:57:46,229
Now, it's not like my children to be secretive.

1338
01:57:46,472 --> 01:57:48,565
We're not being secretive, Father.

1339
01:57:50,242 --> 01:57:53,575
And it's not like my children to be late for dinner.

1340
01:57:53,846 --> 01:57:57,282
- We lost track of the time. - I see.

1341
01:57:58,083 --> 01:58:01,484
Who's going to be the first one to tell me the truth? Friedrich.

1342
01:58:01,754 --> 01:58:03,813
Brigitta. Liesl.

1343
01:58:05,190 --> 01:58:07,420
Where do you think we were, Father?

1344
01:58:13,999 --> 01:58:17,958
If you don't believe us, you must have some idea of where you think we were.

1345
01:58:21,540 --> 01:58:23,337
- Marta. - Yes, Father.

1346
01:58:23,542 --> 01:58:24,804
You tell me.

1347
01:58:26,145 --> 01:58:29,774
Friedrich told you, Father. We were berry picking.

1348
01:58:30,616 --> 01:58:35,280
- I forgot! You were berry picking. - Yes, we love berry picking.

1349
01:58:35,521 --> 01:58:36,613
All afternoon?

1350
01:58:36,855 --> 01:58:38,584
- We picked thousands. - Thousands?

1351
01:58:38,791 --> 01:58:41,692
- They were all over the place. - What kind of berries?

1352
01:58:41,960 --> 01:58:45,225
- Blueberries, sir. - Blueberries.

1353
01:58:47,166 --> 01:58:50,533
It's too early for blueberries.

1354
01:58:52,037 --> 01:58:54,130
- They were strawberries. - Strawberries?

1355
01:58:54,840 --> 01:58:57,536
It's been so cold lately, they turned blue.

1356
01:59:03,382 --> 01:59:05,543
Very well. Show me the berries.

1357
01:59:06,819 --> 01:59:08,013
- We... - Well...

1358
01:59:08,253 --> 01:59:11,017
- Show me the berries you picked. - We don't have them.

1359
01:59:11,256 --> 01:59:13,520
You don't have them? What happened to them?

1360
01:59:13,759 --> 01:59:16,557
- We... - We ate them.

1361
01:59:16,762 --> 01:59:19,356
- You ate them? - Yes!

1362
01:59:19,565 --> 01:59:21,157
- They were so good. - Delicious.

1363
01:59:21,400 --> 01:59:22,594
Very well.

1364
01:59:22,868 --> 01:59:27,999
Since you've obviously stuffed yourselves on thousands of berries...

1365
01:59:28,240 --> 01:59:32,176
...you can't be hungry anymore, so I'll have to tell Frau Schmidt...

1366
01:59:32,411 --> 01:59:35,278
...to skip your dinner.

1367
01:59:44,456 --> 01:59:47,254
It's your fault. We should have told him the truth.

1368
01:59:47,526 --> 01:59:49,494
And made him boiling mad at us?

1369
01:59:49,695 --> 01:59:51,629
It's better than starving to death.

1370
01:59:51,864 --> 01:59:54,731
We didn't do anything wrong. We just wanted to see her.

1371
01:59:56,034 --> 01:59:59,128
My stomach's making noises.

1372
01:59:59,571 --> 02:00:02,404
The least they could have done was to let us say hello.

1373
02:00:03,542 --> 02:00:07,444
- I wonder what grass tastes like. - I feel awful.

1374
02:00:07,880 --> 02:00:12,146
When Fraulein Maria wanted to feel better she used to sing that song.

1375
02:00:12,751 --> 02:00:14,218
Let's try it.

1376
02:00:14,453 --> 02:00:17,115
Raindrops on roses

1377
02:00:17,422 --> 02:00:21,449
And whiskers on kittens

1378
02:00:22,294 --> 02:00:24,888
Bright copper kettles

1379
02:00:25,097 --> 02:00:28,157
And warm woolen mittens

1380
02:00:29,501 --> 02:00:35,462
Brown paper packages Tied up with strings

1381
02:00:35,741 --> 02:00:41,737
These are a few of my favorite things

1382
02:00:41,980 --> 02:00:44,005
Why don't I feel better?

1383
02:00:45,183 --> 02:00:47,481
Girls in white dresses

1384
02:00:47,753 --> 02:00:50,847
With blue satin sashes

1385
02:00:51,123 --> 02:00:56,755
Snowflakes that stay On my nose and eyelashes

1386
02:00:57,129 --> 02:01:00,292
- Silver white winters... - Fraulein Maria's back!

1387
02:01:00,499 --> 02:01:01,796
...that melt into springs

1388
02:01:02,200 --> 02:01:05,465
These are a few of my favorite things

1389
02:01:05,704 --> 02:01:08,798
When the dog bites When the bee stings

1390
02:01:09,007 --> 02:01:11,134
When I'm feeling sad

1391
02:01:11,643 --> 02:01:14,612
I simply remember my favorite things

1392
02:01:14,880 --> 02:01:17,144
And then I don't feel

1393
02:01:17,349 --> 02:01:24,118
So bad

1394
02:01:24,356 --> 02:01:27,382
- Children, I'm so glad to see you. - We missed you.

1395
02:01:27,626 --> 02:01:28,615
I missed you.

1396
02:01:28,894 --> 02:01:31,021
- Kurt, how are you? - Hungry.

1397
02:01:32,564 --> 02:01:35,192
- What happened to your finger? - It got caught.

1398
02:01:35,467 --> 02:01:37,628
- Caught in what? - Friedrich's teeth.

1399
02:01:38,870 --> 02:01:41,031
- Liesl, you all right? - Just fair.

1400
02:01:41,239 --> 02:01:44,231
- Any telegrams been delivered lately? - None at all.

1401
02:01:44,476 --> 02:01:47,912
But I'm learning to accept it. I'll be glad when school begins.

1402
02:01:48,213 --> 02:01:52,912
Liesl, you can't use school to escape your problems. You have to face them.

1403
02:01:53,151 --> 02:01:54,584
I have so much to tell you.

1404
02:01:54,853 --> 02:01:56,844
We have things to tell you too.

1405
02:01:57,189 --> 02:02:00,886
The most important thing is that Father is going to be married.

1406
02:02:01,093 --> 02:02:02,151
Married?

1407
02:02:02,494 --> 02:02:04,519
Yes, to Baroness Schraeder.

1408
02:02:12,437 --> 02:02:13,995
Oh, I see.

1409
02:02:15,841 --> 02:02:19,208
Father, look! Fraulein Maria's back!

1410
02:02:19,444 --> 02:02:21,503
Fraulein Maria's back from the abbey.

1411
02:02:23,715 --> 02:02:24,773
Good evening, captain.

1412
02:02:26,251 --> 02:02:27,548
Good evening.

1413
02:02:30,088 --> 02:02:31,919
Everyone inside for dinner.

1414
02:02:32,224 --> 02:02:33,782
Dinner!

1415
02:02:43,135 --> 02:02:47,868
You left without saying goodbye. Even to the children.

1416
02:02:48,874 --> 02:02:50,398
It was wrong of me. Forgive me.

1417
02:02:52,444 --> 02:02:53,604
Why did you?

1418
02:02:53,812 --> 02:02:56,645
Please don't ask me. The reason no longer exists.

1419
02:02:57,816 --> 02:03:00,910
Fraulein Maria, you've returned.

1420
02:03:02,154 --> 02:03:03,951
Isn't it wonderful, Georg?

1421
02:03:07,259 --> 02:03:09,489
I wish you every happiness, baroness.

1422
02:03:09,728 --> 02:03:12,424
You too, captain. The children say you're to marry.

1423
02:03:12,664 --> 02:03:13,790
Thank you, my dear.

1424
02:03:16,334 --> 02:03:19,895
You are back to stay?

1425
02:03:21,973 --> 02:03:25,306
Only until arrangements can be made for another governess.

1426
02:04:20,999 --> 02:04:22,626
There you are.

1427
02:04:37,015 --> 02:04:39,483
I must speak to cook about the schnitzel.

1428
02:04:39,751 --> 02:04:43,050
It is entirely too delicious for my figure.

1429
02:04:43,488 --> 02:04:46,423
And it makes you much too quiet at the dinner table.

1430
02:04:46,691 --> 02:04:48,682
Or was it the wine?

1431
02:04:48,927 --> 02:04:50,758
Undoubtedly the wine.

1432
02:04:53,331 --> 02:04:55,595
You have no idea the trouble I'm having...

1433
02:04:55,867 --> 02:04:58,597
...trying to decide on a wedding present for you.

1434
02:04:58,904 --> 02:05:01,065
Oh, I know. I'm enough.

1435
02:05:01,339 --> 02:05:04,934
But I do want you to have some little trifle for the occasion.

1436
02:05:05,177 --> 02:05:07,509
At first I thought of a fountain pen...

1437
02:05:07,746 --> 02:05:10,010
...but you've already got one.

1438
02:05:10,282 --> 02:05:13,217
Then I thought perhaps a villa in the south of France...

1439
02:05:13,451 --> 02:05:16,113
...but they are so difficult to gift-wrap.

1440
02:05:16,388 --> 02:05:18,788
Oh, Georg, how do you feel about yachts?

1441
02:05:19,090 --> 02:05:21,354
A long, sleek one for the Mediterranean...

1442
02:05:21,593 --> 02:05:24,357
...or a tiny one for your bathtub, huh?

1443
02:05:26,531 --> 02:05:28,556
- Elsa. - Where to go on our honeymoon?

1444
02:05:28,800 --> 02:05:30,392
Now, that's a real problem.

1445
02:05:30,602 --> 02:05:33,969
A trip around the world would be lovely. And then I said:

1446
02:05:34,272 --> 02:05:37,105
"Oh, Elsa, there must be someplace better to go."

1447
02:05:37,375 --> 02:05:39,809
- But don't worry, darling, I'Il... - Elsa.

1448
02:05:40,478 --> 02:05:41,740
Yes, Georg.

1449
02:05:42,747 --> 02:05:44,078
It's no use...

1450
02:05:45,283 --> 02:05:46,648
...you and I.

1451
02:05:48,220 --> 02:05:51,451
I'm being dishonest to both of us...

1452
02:05:52,791 --> 02:05:54,452
...and utterly unfair to you.

1453
02:05:59,731 --> 02:06:02,461
- When two people talk of marriage... - No, don't.

1454
02:06:03,335 --> 02:06:05,428
Don't say another word, please.

1455
02:06:08,740 --> 02:06:13,768
You see, there are other things I've been thinking of.

1456
02:06:14,679 --> 02:06:19,412
Fond as I am of you, I really don't think you're the right man for me.

1457
02:06:21,953 --> 02:06:24,444
You're much too independent.

1458
02:06:24,756 --> 02:06:29,455
And I need someone who needs me desperately...

1459
02:06:29,761 --> 02:06:32,753
...or at least needs my money desperately.

1460
02:06:34,933 --> 02:06:39,836
I've enjoyed every moment we've had together and I do thank you for that.

1461
02:06:42,607 --> 02:06:44,507
Now, if you'll forgive me...

1462
02:06:44,709 --> 02:06:46,768
...I'll go inside, pack my little bags...

1463
02:06:47,012 --> 02:06:49,503
...and return to Vienna where I belong.

1464
02:06:54,886 --> 02:06:56,717
And somewhere out there...

1465
02:06:57,022 --> 02:07:01,391
...is a young lady who, I think...

1466
02:07:01,660 --> 02:07:02,888
...will never be a nun.

1467
02:07:15,040 --> 02:07:17,372
Auf Wiedersehen, darling.

1468
02:07:43,101 --> 02:07:44,261
Hello.

1469
02:07:50,075 --> 02:07:53,670
I thought I just might find you here.

1470
02:07:57,849 --> 02:08:00,113
Was there something you wanted?

1471
02:08:00,552 --> 02:08:03,680
No, no, no. Sit down, please.

1472
02:08:04,622 --> 02:08:05,953
Please.

1473
02:08:11,096 --> 02:08:12,427
May I?

1474
02:08:24,809 --> 02:08:29,542
You know, I was thinking and I was wondering two things:

1475
02:08:30,715 --> 02:08:34,947
Why did you run away to the abbey?

1476
02:08:35,787 --> 02:08:40,451
And what was it that made you come back?

1477
02:08:42,127 --> 02:08:46,587
Well, I had an obligation to fulfill...

1478
02:08:46,798 --> 02:08:48,925
...and I came back to fulfill it.

1479
02:08:49,567 --> 02:08:51,000
Is that all?

1480
02:08:52,337 --> 02:08:54,498
And I missed the children.

1481
02:08:54,839 --> 02:08:55,999
Yes.

1482
02:08:57,275 --> 02:09:00,176
- Only the children? - No. Yes.

1483
02:09:00,412 --> 02:09:04,246
- Isn't it right that I missed them? - Oh, yes. Yes, of course.

1484
02:09:04,449 --> 02:09:07,077
I was only hoping that perhaps you...

1485
02:09:08,186 --> 02:09:09,949
Perhaps you might...

1486
02:09:11,689 --> 02:09:12,917
Yes?

1487
02:09:14,692 --> 02:09:19,994
Well, nothing was the same when you were away...

1488
02:09:20,765 --> 02:09:23,996
...and it'll be all wrong again after you leave...

1489
02:09:24,202 --> 02:09:28,866
...and I just thought perhaps you might change your mind.

1490
02:09:32,944 --> 02:09:37,176
Well, I'm sure the baroness will be able to make things fine for you.

1491
02:09:37,449 --> 02:09:38,780
Maria...

1492
02:09:40,885 --> 02:09:44,377
- There isn't going to be any baroness. - There isn't?

1493
02:09:46,791 --> 02:09:48,156
No.

1494
02:09:48,460 --> 02:09:50,223
I don't understand.

1495
02:09:52,630 --> 02:09:56,726
Well, we've called off our engagement, you see, and...

1496
02:09:57,001 --> 02:10:00,459
- Oh, I'm sorry. - Yes. You are?

1497
02:10:01,639 --> 02:10:03,732
- You did? - Yes.

1498
02:10:04,876 --> 02:10:09,404
Well, you can't marry someone when you're...

1499
02:10:11,983 --> 02:10:14,042
...in love with someone else...

1500
02:10:17,422 --> 02:10:18,855
...can you?

1501
02:10:53,725 --> 02:10:56,023
The Reverend Mother always says:

1502
02:10:56,261 --> 02:10:59,697
"When the Lord closes a door, somewhere He opens a window."

1503
02:11:07,786 --> 02:11:10,812
What else does the Reverend Mother say?

1504
02:11:11,756 --> 02:11:14,156
That you have to look for your life.

1505
02:11:15,827 --> 02:11:18,387
Is that why you came back?

1506
02:11:22,434 --> 02:11:23,901
And have you found it...

1507
02:11:24,903 --> 02:11:26,063
...Maria?

1508
02:11:27,839 --> 02:11:29,830
I think I have.

1509
02:11:32,577 --> 02:11:33,976
I know I have.

1510
02:11:36,481 --> 02:11:38,142
I love you.

1511
02:11:42,120 --> 02:11:43,985
Oh, can this be happening to me?

1512
02:11:47,359 --> 02:11:52,763
Perhaps I had a wicked childhood

1513
02:11:54,266 --> 02:11:59,499
Perhaps I had a miserable youth

1514
02:12:01,373 --> 02:12:07,312
But somewhere In my wicked, miserable past

1515
02:12:07,812 --> 02:12:13,614
There must have been a moment of truth

1516
02:12:14,552 --> 02:12:21,321
For here you are Standing there loving me

1517
02:12:22,060 --> 02:12:28,056
Whether or not you should

1518
02:12:28,700 --> 02:12:35,503
So somewhere in my youth or childhood

1519
02:12:36,374 --> 02:12:44,008
I must have done something good

1520
02:12:45,250 --> 02:12:48,219
Nothing comes from nothing

1521
02:12:49,354 --> 02:12:53,222
Nothing ever could

1522
02:12:54,059 --> 02:13:02,933
So somewhere in my youth or childhood

1523
02:13:04,502 --> 02:13:14,002
I must have done something good

1524
02:13:14,879 --> 02:13:19,714
Do you know when I first started loving you?

1525
02:13:20,118 --> 02:13:24,020
That night at dinner, when you sat on that ridiculous pine cone.

1526
02:13:24,255 --> 02:13:25,552
What?

1527
02:13:26,891 --> 02:13:30,349
I knew the first time you blew that silly whistle.

1528
02:13:31,262 --> 02:13:33,253
Oh, my love.

1529
02:13:37,035 --> 02:13:44,942
For here you are Standing there loving me

1530
02:13:46,911 --> 02:13:52,747
Whether or not you should

1531
02:13:54,119 --> 02:14:01,150
So somewhere in my youth or childhood

1532
02:14:01,960 --> 02:14:09,662
I must have done something good

1533
02:14:10,835 --> 02:14:14,327
Nothing comes from nothing

1534
02:14:15,073 --> 02:14:18,099
Nothing ever could

1535
02:14:18,343 --> 02:14:24,145
So somewhere in my youth...

1536
02:14:24,416 --> 02:14:26,646
...or childhood

1537
02:14:29,754 --> 02:14:36,284
I must have done something

1538
02:14:38,329 --> 02:14:50,969
Something good

1539
02:14:57,682 --> 02:14:59,206
Maria.

1540
02:15:01,052 --> 02:15:05,648
Is there anyone I should go to, to ask permission to marry you?

1541
02:15:09,561 --> 02:15:12,121
- Why don't we ask... - The children?

1542
02:17:00,638 --> 02:17:04,665
How do you solve a problem like Maria?

1543
02:17:05,476 --> 02:17:09,173
How do you catch a cloud And pin it down?

1544
02:17:10,148 --> 02:17:14,312
How do you find a word That means Maria?

1545
02:17:14,752 --> 02:17:15,741
A flibbertigibbet

1546
02:17:15,987 --> 02:17:19,252
A will-o'-the-wisp A clown

1547
02:17:19,457 --> 02:17:24,019
Many a thing you know You'd like to tell her

1548
02:17:24,462 --> 02:17:28,489
Many a thing she ought to understand

1549
02:17:29,200 --> 02:17:33,500
But how do you make her stay And listen to all you say?

1550
02:17:33,871 --> 02:17:37,807
How do you keep a wave upon the sand?

1551
02:17:38,142 --> 02:17:43,136
Oh, how do you solve A problem like Maria?

1552
02:17:43,514 --> 02:17:50,147
How do you hold a moonbeam In your hand?

1553
02:19:56,247 --> 02:19:57,805
Herr Detweiler!

1554
02:20:00,418 --> 02:20:03,080
- Heil Hitler. - Oh, good afternoon, Herr Zeller.

1555
02:20:03,321 --> 02:20:06,620
Perhaps you've not heard. I am now the Gauleiter.

1556
02:20:06,924 --> 02:20:08,448
Heil Hitler.

1557
02:20:09,360 --> 02:20:10,520
Heil Hitler.

1558
02:20:10,828 --> 02:20:13,092
I've come from Captain von Trapp's house.

1559
02:20:13,531 --> 02:20:17,126
The only one in the area not flying the Third Reich flag...

1560
02:20:17,368 --> 02:20:18,630
...since the Anschluss.

1561
02:20:18,836 --> 02:20:20,997
- But we have dealt with that. - I don't...

1562
02:20:21,272 --> 02:20:24,207
The housekeeper told me that I would find you here.

1563
02:20:24,475 --> 02:20:26,170
The only thing she'd tell me.

1564
02:20:26,677 --> 02:20:29,202
What kind of information are you looking for?

1565
02:20:29,480 --> 02:20:31,345
When will the captain return?

1566
02:20:31,883 --> 02:20:35,819
Well, he's on his honeymoon trip. He's not been in touch with us.

1567
02:20:36,053 --> 02:20:40,888
Am I to believe he hasn't communicated with his children in over a month?

1568
02:20:41,159 --> 02:20:43,059
How many men do you know...

1569
02:20:43,327 --> 02:20:46,626
...who communicate with their children while honeymooning?

1570
02:20:47,532 --> 02:20:51,229
Upon his return, he'll fill his proper position in the new order.

1571
02:20:51,536 --> 02:20:53,902
Naturally. And may I congratulate you...

1572
02:20:54,138 --> 02:20:58,802
...and your people in allowing the festival to go on tonight as planned.

1573
02:20:59,343 --> 02:21:02,801
Why should it not go on? Nothing in Austria has changed.

1574
02:21:03,047 --> 02:21:06,448
Singing and music will show this to the world.

1575
02:21:06,651 --> 02:21:08,346
Austria is the same.

1576
02:21:09,220 --> 02:21:10,585
Heil Hitler.

1577
02:21:12,757 --> 02:21:14,349
Heil Hitler.

1578
02:21:16,027 --> 02:21:17,255
Come, let's go home.

1579
02:21:17,495 --> 02:21:20,987
- Why was he so cross? - Everybody's cross these days.

1580
02:21:21,199 --> 02:21:24,566
Maybe the flag with the black spider makes people nervous.

1581
02:21:24,769 --> 02:21:27,704
- Will Father be in trouble? - He doesn't have to be.

1582
02:21:27,939 --> 02:21:30,669
The thing to do is to get along with everybody.

1583
02:21:30,908 --> 02:21:33,103
Remember that tonight at the concert.

1584
02:21:33,344 --> 02:21:36,245
Are we really going to sing before a lot of people?

1585
02:21:36,447 --> 02:21:38,540
Look. The von Trapp Family Singers:

1586
02:21:38,749 --> 02:21:43,345
Liesl, Friedrich, Louisa, Brigitta, Kurt, Marta and Gretl.

1587
02:21:43,554 --> 02:21:47,923
- Why am I always last? - Because you are the most important.

1588
02:21:48,626 --> 02:21:50,253
There we go.

1589
02:21:56,133 --> 02:21:59,591
Are you sure Father will approve of our singing in public?

1590
02:21:59,804 --> 02:22:02,102
He'll be pleased and proud.

1591
02:22:02,573 --> 02:22:05,041
- Liesl, do you think so? - Don't you trust me?

1592
02:22:05,243 --> 02:22:06,267
No.

1593
02:22:06,477 --> 02:22:08,570
You're a very intelligent girl.

1594
02:22:09,113 --> 02:22:11,274
Liesl. Liesl!

1595
02:22:12,216 --> 02:22:13,410
Rolfe!

1596
02:22:14,418 --> 02:22:16,443
I'm so glad to see you. It's been su...

1597
02:22:16,654 --> 02:22:17,746
Good afternoon.

1598
02:22:18,155 --> 02:22:21,090
Give this to your father as soon as he's home.

1599
02:22:21,759 --> 02:22:23,624
- He's on his honeymoon. - I know.

1600
02:22:23,828 --> 02:22:27,161
- You do? - We make it our business to know all.

1601
02:22:27,899 --> 02:22:30,459
- Who's "we"? - See that he gets it.

1602
02:22:30,668 --> 02:22:33,000
- What is it? - It's a telegram from Berlin.

1603
02:22:33,838 --> 02:22:36,329
Don't you want to deliver it yourself?

1604
02:22:36,807 --> 02:22:39,435
I'm occupied with more important matters.

1605
02:22:39,644 --> 02:22:42,135
And your father had better be too.

1606
02:22:42,413 --> 02:22:43,903
But, Rolfe!

1607
02:23:07,004 --> 02:23:08,665
Father!

1608
02:23:08,940 --> 02:23:11,602
- We didn't expect you so soon. - Hello, hello!

1609
02:23:11,842 --> 02:23:14,640
We didn't expect you home until next week!

1610
02:23:14,845 --> 02:23:20,283
- Did you bring souvenirs from Paris? - Hello! How are you?

1611
02:23:21,385 --> 02:23:22,682
Why didn't you call us?

1612
02:23:22,887 --> 02:23:24,821
We couldn't get through.

1613
02:23:25,122 --> 02:23:27,056
I had nothing to do with that.

1614
02:23:27,325 --> 02:23:29,350
We came back as fast as we could.

1615
02:23:29,660 --> 02:23:31,821
Well, well, well! We missed you!

1616
02:23:32,063 --> 02:23:34,497
- We missed you! - We missed kissing you.

1617
02:23:34,699 --> 02:23:37,532
We missed all the noise in the morning.

1618
02:23:37,802 --> 02:23:42,000
- Mostly, we missed hearing you sing. - Oh, you came back just in time.

1619
02:23:42,206 --> 02:23:43,969
Look, Fraulein Maria...

1620
02:23:44,175 --> 02:23:45,802
I mean Mother.

1621
02:23:46,210 --> 02:23:48,701
We're going to sing in the festival tonight.

1622
02:23:48,913 --> 02:23:51,040
We've been having a lovely time!

1623
02:23:51,315 --> 02:23:53,374
We've been rehearsing all...

1624
02:23:54,885 --> 02:23:57,217
Surprise! Surprise!

1625
02:23:57,888 --> 02:24:00,379
Surprises for you on the terrace.

1626
02:24:03,427 --> 02:24:04,826
We'll talk about this.

1627
02:24:05,029 --> 02:24:09,329
I would've told you but you were away. I had to make a last-minute decision.

1628
02:24:09,600 --> 02:24:12,091
I was fortunate to enter them at all.

1629
02:24:12,336 --> 02:24:17,069
They'll be the talk of the festival. Imagine, seven children in one family!

1630
02:24:17,274 --> 02:24:18,901
Max!

1631
02:24:19,510 --> 02:24:22,343
Somehow I recall having made it quite clear to you...

1632
02:24:22,613 --> 02:24:25,275
...how I feel about my family singing in public!

1633
02:24:25,549 --> 02:24:27,244
The committee was enchanted.

1634
02:24:27,451 --> 02:24:30,614
- What did they say? - I have never heard such enthusiasm.

1635
02:24:30,888 --> 02:24:35,188
- Don't you think just this once...? - Absolutely out of the question.

1636
02:24:35,426 --> 02:24:39,556
- Georg, this is for Austria. - For Austria?

1637
02:24:39,930 --> 02:24:43,195
- There is no Austria! - But the Anschluss was peaceful.

1638
02:24:43,434 --> 02:24:46,892
- Let's at least be grateful for that. - Grateful?

1639
02:24:48,773 --> 02:24:50,434
You know, Max...

1640
02:24:51,308 --> 02:24:54,573
...sometimes I don't believe I know you.

1641
02:24:57,248 --> 02:24:58,613
Father, I forgot.

1642
02:24:59,450 --> 02:25:01,042
This is for you.

1643
02:25:10,828 --> 02:25:14,821
Maria, he has got to at least pretend to work with these people.

1644
02:25:15,099 --> 02:25:16,623
You must convince him.

1645
02:25:16,834 --> 02:25:19,598
Max, I can't ask him to be less than he is.

1646
02:25:19,837 --> 02:25:23,136
Then I'll talk to him. If the children don't sing, well...

1647
02:25:23,407 --> 02:25:25,637
...it will be a reflection on Austria.

1648
02:25:26,444 --> 02:25:29,811
Oh, I know. It wouldn't do me any good either.

1649
02:25:34,985 --> 02:25:37,647
Mother? That sounds so nice.

1650
02:25:37,922 --> 02:25:40,652
- I like calling you "Mother." - I like hearing it.

1651
02:25:40,858 --> 02:25:44,589
You love Father very much. I can tell you do.

1652
02:25:44,795 --> 02:25:45,591
Very much.

1653
02:25:45,863 --> 02:25:49,162
Mother, what do you do when you think you love someone?

1654
02:25:49,867 --> 02:25:55,169
I mean, when you stop loving someone or he stops loving you?

1655
02:25:57,775 --> 02:25:59,834
Well, you cry a little.

1656
02:26:00,277 --> 02:26:02,370
Then you wait for the sun to come out.

1657
02:26:02,680 --> 02:26:04,011
It always does.

1658
02:26:04,281 --> 02:26:07,842
There are so many things I think I should know but I don't.

1659
02:26:08,052 --> 02:26:10,020
- I really don't. - How can you?

1660
02:26:10,287 --> 02:26:12,482
Sometimes I feel the world is ending.

1661
02:26:12,723 --> 02:26:15,954
- Then you feel it's just beginning? - Yes!

1662
02:26:16,160 --> 02:26:20,392
It was that way with me. And for you it will be just as wonderful.

1663
02:26:21,065 --> 02:26:22,965
Do you really think so?

1664
02:26:23,868 --> 02:26:27,804
When you're 16 going on 17

1665
02:26:28,072 --> 02:26:31,667
Waiting for life to start

1666
02:26:32,343 --> 02:26:36,177
Somebody kind Who touches your mind

1667
02:26:36,413 --> 02:26:40,713
Will suddenly touch your heart

1668
02:26:41,152 --> 02:26:42,847
When that happens

1669
02:26:43,320 --> 02:26:45,254
After it happens

1670
02:26:45,489 --> 02:26:49,357
Nothing is quite the same

1671
02:26:49,593 --> 02:26:51,151
Somehow I know

1672
02:26:51,428 --> 02:26:53,555
I'll jump up and go

1673
02:26:53,764 --> 02:26:58,064
If ever he calls my name

1674
02:26:58,335 --> 02:27:02,237
Gone are your old ideas of life

1675
02:27:02,506 --> 02:27:06,704
The old ideas grow dim

1676
02:27:06,944 --> 02:27:11,347
Lo and behold You're someone's wife

1677
02:27:12,283 --> 02:27:18,279
And you belong to him

1678
02:27:18,589 --> 02:27:22,889
You may think this kind of adventure

1679
02:27:23,093 --> 02:27:26,961
Never may come to you

1680
02:27:28,065 --> 02:27:33,435
Darling, 16 going on 17

1681
02:27:34,271 --> 02:27:38,401
Wait a year...

1682
02:27:39,210 --> 02:27:44,443
- I'll wait a year ...or two

1683
02:27:44,882 --> 02:27:52,220
Just wait a year...

1684
02:27:53,090 --> 02:28:01,725
...or two

1685
02:28:04,134 --> 02:28:05,726
Liesl.

1686
02:28:22,186 --> 02:28:23,517
What is it?

1687
02:28:24,455 --> 02:28:25,820
Berlin.

1688
02:28:26,290 --> 02:28:28,155
They've offered me a commission.

1689
02:28:28,425 --> 02:28:30,950
I've been requested to accept immediately...

1690
02:28:31,195 --> 02:28:35,188
...and report to their naval base at Bremerhaven tomorrow.

1691
02:28:35,799 --> 02:28:39,792
I knew this would happen. I didn't think it would be so soon.

1692
02:28:40,037 --> 02:28:43,529
To refuse them would be fatal for all of us.

1693
02:28:44,775 --> 02:28:48,541
And joining them would be unthinkable.

1694
02:28:54,718 --> 02:28:56,481
Get the children all together.

1695
02:28:56,820 --> 02:29:00,017
Don't say anything to worry them. Just get them ready.

1696
02:29:00,991 --> 02:29:03,357
We've got to get out of Austria...

1697
02:29:05,029 --> 02:29:06,690
...and this house...

1698
02:29:09,033 --> 02:29:10,466
...tonight.

1699
02:29:54,378 --> 02:29:56,778
This strains my back and breaks my heart...

1700
02:29:57,047 --> 02:29:59,880
...when I think of the children missing the festival.

1701
02:30:00,184 --> 02:30:02,846
By your announcement we'll be over the border.

1702
02:30:03,087 --> 02:30:05,521
Do you appreciate the sacrifice I'm making?

1703
02:30:05,723 --> 02:30:07,020
You have no choice.

1704
02:30:07,257 --> 02:30:10,090
I know. That's why I'm making it.

1705
02:30:10,794 --> 02:30:12,921
Why doesn't Father turn the motor on?

1706
02:30:13,130 --> 02:30:16,566
Because he doesn't want anyone to hear us.

1707
02:30:20,204 --> 02:30:22,638
What will Frau Schmidt and Franz say?

1708
02:30:22,906 --> 02:30:26,433
They'll be able to answer honestly they didn't know anything.

1709
02:30:26,643 --> 02:30:30,875
- Will we be coming back here? - Someday, Liesl. I do hope someday.

1710
02:30:31,115 --> 02:30:36,052
Are Father and Uncle Max going to push the car all the way to Switzerland?

1711
02:31:02,846 --> 02:31:05,246
Something wrong with your car, captain?

1712
02:31:05,582 --> 02:31:07,846
Yes, we couldn't get it started.

1713
02:31:11,622 --> 02:31:12,850
Karl.

1714
02:31:14,825 --> 02:31:18,317
Fix Captain von Trapp's car so that it will start.

1715
02:31:41,518 --> 02:31:43,315
Excellent, Karl.

1716
02:31:46,690 --> 02:31:49,853
I've not asked you where you and your family are going.

1717
02:31:50,360 --> 02:31:52,487
Nor have you asked me why I'm here.

1718
02:31:52,696 --> 02:31:56,462
Apparently we both suffer from a deplorable lack of curiosity.

1719
02:31:57,334 --> 02:31:59,802
You never answered the telegram...

1720
02:32:00,037 --> 02:32:03,336
...from the Admiral of the Navy of the Third Reich.

1721
02:32:03,574 --> 02:32:06,042
I was under the impression, Herr Zeller...

1722
02:32:06,310 --> 02:32:09,802
...that the contents of telegrams in Austria are private!

1723
02:32:10,514 --> 02:32:14,041
At least, the Austria I know.

1724
02:32:15,185 --> 02:32:16,812
I have my orders...

1725
02:32:17,054 --> 02:32:19,215
...to take you to Bremerhaven tonight...

1726
02:32:19,490 --> 02:32:21,685
...where you will accept your commission.

1727
02:32:22,826 --> 02:32:28,264
I'm afraid that's going to be quite impossible.

1728
02:32:28,866 --> 02:32:30,595
You see, we...

1729
02:32:31,168 --> 02:32:34,001
...all of us, the entire family, will be...

1730
02:32:35,072 --> 02:32:37,097
...singing in the festival tonight.

1731
02:32:37,407 --> 02:32:39,875
As a matter of fact, we're going now.

1732
02:32:40,511 --> 02:32:43,378
We couldn't possibly let them down now.

1733
02:32:43,580 --> 02:32:46,549
- I just hope we're not too late. - Yes.

1734
02:32:46,783 --> 02:32:49,684
You ask me to believe that you, Captain von Trapp...

1735
02:32:49,920 --> 02:32:51,387
...are singing in a concert?

1736
02:32:51,788 --> 02:32:55,918
Believe me, it will be a performance beyond anything even I've dreamt of.

1737
02:32:56,293 --> 02:33:00,923
Like you, Herr Zeller, I, too, am a man of hidden talents.

1738
02:33:01,632 --> 02:33:02,963
Yes.

1739
02:33:03,233 --> 02:33:05,724
Here, program.

1740
02:33:10,741 --> 02:33:13,073
It says only the names of the children.

1741
02:33:13,310 --> 02:33:16,575
It says the von Trapp Family Singers...

1742
02:33:16,813 --> 02:33:19,873
...and I am the head of the von Trapp family, am I not?

1743
02:33:22,152 --> 02:33:25,952
And these travel clothes that you're all wearing?

1744
02:33:26,790 --> 02:33:28,314
Our costumes, naturally.

1745
02:33:28,592 --> 02:33:31,993
This night air is not good for the children's voices.

1746
02:33:38,235 --> 02:33:41,762
Well, a slight delay in my orders will not be serious.

1747
02:33:42,973 --> 02:33:44,497
Therefore...

1748
02:33:45,342 --> 02:33:46,969
...you will sing.

1749
02:33:47,911 --> 02:33:49,902
You will all sing.

1750
02:33:50,280 --> 02:33:52,805
But only because that's what I want.

1751
02:33:53,750 --> 02:33:57,186
It will demonstrate that nothing in Austria has changed.

1752
02:33:57,921 --> 02:34:00,116
And when you have finished singing...

1753
02:34:00,424 --> 02:34:03,587
...you, Captain von Trapp, will be taken to Bremerhaven.

1754
02:34:04,861 --> 02:34:07,591
Now, if you will all get into your car...

1755
02:34:07,831 --> 02:34:11,665
...we will escort the von Trapp Family Singers to the festival.

1756
02:34:12,536 --> 02:34:14,697
No escort will be necessary.

1757
02:34:14,938 --> 02:34:17,429
Necessary? A pleasure, captain.

1758
02:34:18,342 --> 02:34:22,210
After all, we would not want you to get lost in the crowds.

1759
02:34:23,447 --> 02:34:24,937
Would we?

1760
02:34:25,616 --> 02:34:26,776
No.

1761
02:34:43,000 --> 02:34:46,163
Sew, a needle pulling thread

1762
02:34:46,370 --> 02:34:49,567
La, a note to follow sew

1763
02:34:49,840 --> 02:34:53,298
Tea, a drink with jam and bread

1764
02:34:53,510 --> 02:34:57,310
A drink with jam and bread

1765
02:35:06,890 --> 02:35:09,051
Tea with jam Jam and bread

1766
02:35:14,931 --> 02:35:18,264
- With jam - A, B, C

1767
02:35:18,502 --> 02:35:21,733
- With jam - Do-re-mi

1768
02:35:21,938 --> 02:35:25,533
Tea with jam and bread

1769
02:35:25,776 --> 02:35:27,107
With jam and bread

1770
02:35:27,377 --> 02:35:28,901
With jam With jam...

1771
02:35:29,112 --> 02:35:37,918
...and bread

1772
02:35:59,910 --> 02:36:03,038
My fellow Austrians...

1773
02:36:04,314 --> 02:36:08,876
...I shall not be seeing you again, perhaps for a very long time.

1774
02:36:10,287 --> 02:36:11,948
I would like to sing for you now...

1775
02:36:13,557 --> 02:36:15,115
...a love song.

1776
02:36:17,094 --> 02:36:19,289
I know you share this love.

1777
02:36:20,597 --> 02:36:24,294
I pray that you will never let it die.

1778
02:36:37,080 --> 02:36:40,607
Edelweiss

1779
02:36:40,817 --> 02:36:44,014
Edelweiss

1780
02:36:44,287 --> 02:36:50,021
Every morning you greet me

1781
02:36:50,427 --> 02:36:53,487
Small and white

1782
02:36:53,764 --> 02:36:56,528
Clean and bright

1783
02:36:57,100 --> 02:37:02,197
You look happy to meet me

1784
02:37:02,973 --> 02:37:04,998
Blossom of snow

1785
02:37:05,275 --> 02:37:08,870
May you bloom and grow

1786
02:37:09,112 --> 02:37:14,778
Bloom and grow forever

1787
02:37:16,286 --> 02:37:18,777
Edelweiss

1788
02:37:19,022 --> 02:37:21,650
Edelweiss

1789
02:37:21,858 --> 02:37:27,854
Bless my homeland forever

1790
02:37:32,369 --> 02:37:35,463
Edelweiss

1791
02:37:35,705 --> 02:37:37,036
Edel...

1792
02:37:44,414 --> 02:37:47,508
Small and white

1793
02:37:47,717 --> 02:37:50,584
Clean and bright

1794
02:37:50,821 --> 02:37:56,157
You look happy to meet me

1795
02:37:56,993 --> 02:37:58,961
Blossom of snow

1796
02:37:59,162 --> 02:38:02,563
May you bloom and grow

1797
02:38:03,233 --> 02:38:09,229
Bloom and grow forever

1798
02:38:09,706 --> 02:38:12,607
Edelweiss

1799
02:38:12,909 --> 02:38:15,673
Edelweiss

1800
02:38:16,279 --> 02:38:24,516
Bless my homeland forever

1801
02:38:42,239 --> 02:38:43,797
I think it'll work.

1802
02:38:44,541 --> 02:38:46,304
I shall miss all of you.

1803
02:38:46,810 --> 02:38:49,244
I shall miss the money I could have made with you.

1804
02:38:52,649 --> 02:38:54,207
Thank you, ladies and gentlemen.

1805
02:38:54,951 --> 02:38:57,613
The competition has come to its conclusion...

1806
02:38:57,888 --> 02:39:00,982
...except, we don't know yet what that conclusion will be.

1807
02:39:01,958 --> 02:39:04,483
And while the judges arrive at their decision...

1808
02:39:04,761 --> 02:39:07,787
...I have been given permission to offer you an encore.

1809
02:39:08,064 --> 02:39:11,261
This will be the last opportunity the von Trapps will have...

1810
02:39:11,501 --> 02:39:13,901
...of singing together for a long, long time.

1811
02:39:14,971 --> 02:39:18,964
Even now, officials are waiting in this auditorium...

1812
02:39:19,242 --> 02:39:21,972
...to escort Captain von Trapp to his new command...

1813
02:39:22,178 --> 02:39:25,739
...in the naval forces of the Third Reich.

1814
02:39:30,420 --> 02:39:34,948
And so, ladies and gentlemen, the family von Trapp again...

1815
02:39:35,592 --> 02:39:37,856
...to bid you farewell.

1816
02:39:45,101 --> 02:39:48,696
There's a sad sort of clanging From the clock in the hall

1817
02:39:48,972 --> 02:39:52,305
And the bells in the steeple too

1818
02:39:52,809 --> 02:39:56,677
And up in the nursery An absurd little bird

1819
02:39:56,880 --> 02:39:59,314
Is popping out to say "coo-coo"

1820
02:39:59,516 --> 02:40:01,177
Coo-coo

1821
02:40:01,451 --> 02:40:02,440
Coo-coo

1822
02:40:02,719 --> 02:40:04,311
Regretfully they tell us

1823
02:40:04,521 --> 02:40:06,318
But firmly they compel us

1824
02:40:06,556 --> 02:40:09,320
To say goodbye

1825
02:40:09,526 --> 02:40:14,691
To you

1826
02:40:17,667 --> 02:40:21,194
So long, farewell Auf Wiedersehen, good night

1827
02:40:21,471 --> 02:40:25,202
We hate to go And miss this pretty sight

1828
02:40:31,381 --> 02:40:34,976
So long, farewell Auf Wiedersehen, adieu

1829
02:40:35,185 --> 02:40:38,848
Adieu, adieu To you and you and you

1830
02:40:45,161 --> 02:40:48,756
So long, farewell Auf Wiedersehen, goodbye

1831
02:40:48,999 --> 02:40:50,591
We flit, we float

1832
02:40:50,867 --> 02:40:52,528
We fleetly flee, we fly

1833
02:40:58,908 --> 02:41:02,708
So long, farewell Auf Wiedersehen, goodbye

1834
02:41:02,912 --> 02:41:06,279
The sun has gone to bed And so must I

1835
02:41:06,549 --> 02:41:10,349
Goodbye

1836
02:41:10,587 --> 02:41:16,287
Goodbye

1837
02:41:16,526 --> 02:41:21,725
Goodbye

1838
02:41:21,965 --> 02:41:29,133
Goodbye

1839
02:42:00,937 --> 02:42:05,067
Ladies and gentlemen, I have here the decision of our distinguished judges.

1840
02:42:05,275 --> 02:42:07,835
We will start with the award for third prize.

1841
02:42:08,478 --> 02:42:10,810
For this honor, the judges have named...

1842
02:42:11,081 --> 02:42:15,677
...the first soloist of the choir of St. Agatha's Church in Murback.

1843
02:42:15,952 --> 02:42:18,182
Fraulein Schweiger.

1844
02:42:55,125 --> 02:42:59,061
Second prize to The Toby Reiser Quintet.

1845
02:43:27,023 --> 02:43:31,187
And the first prize, the highest honor in all Austria...

1846
02:43:31,427 --> 02:43:34,521
...the von Trapp Family Singers.

1847
02:43:46,910 --> 02:43:48,571
The family von Trapp.

1848
02:44:03,193 --> 02:44:04,251
They're gone!

1849
02:44:22,946 --> 02:44:24,379
Come with me.

1850
02:44:28,218 --> 02:44:30,209
Quickly, quickly.

1851
02:44:31,120 --> 02:44:33,315
I have a place you can hide.

1852
02:44:34,057 --> 02:44:37,322
Slowly, slowly.

1853
02:44:48,304 --> 02:44:49,999
Open this gate.

1854
02:44:51,140 --> 02:44:52,732
Good evening.

1855
02:44:55,245 --> 02:44:56,678
Hurry up, woman.

1856
02:45:16,532 --> 02:45:17,794
Two men in there.

1857
02:45:18,001 --> 02:45:19,866
Six of you cover the yard.

1858
02:45:20,103 --> 02:45:22,333
You two, cover the corridor.

1859
02:45:36,819 --> 02:45:40,380
Reverend Mother, we didn't realize we put the abbey in this danger.

1860
02:45:40,657 --> 02:45:43,182
No, Maria, it was right for you to come here.

1861
02:45:43,393 --> 02:45:45,293
We thought we might borrow your car.

1862
02:45:45,495 --> 02:45:47,395
I'm afraid our car will do you no good now.

1863
02:45:47,997 --> 02:45:49,658
I've been listening to the wires.

1864
02:45:49,866 --> 02:45:52,391
The borders have just been closed.

1865
02:45:58,241 --> 02:46:00,539
All right, if the borders are closed...

1866
02:46:01,844 --> 02:46:05,143
...then we'll drive up into the hills and go over the mountains on foot.

1867
02:46:05,748 --> 02:46:07,739
- The children... - We'll help them.

1868
02:46:08,017 --> 02:46:10,178
We can do it without help, Father.

1869
02:46:11,220 --> 02:46:12,585
Maria.

1870
02:46:13,323 --> 02:46:15,917
You will not be alone. Remember:

1871
02:46:16,159 --> 02:46:19,253
"I will lift up mine eyes unto the hills from whence cometh my help."

1872
02:46:20,229 --> 02:46:21,321
Yes, Mother.

1873
02:46:22,699 --> 02:46:24,860
- I'm scared. - Me too.

1874
02:46:36,946 --> 02:46:38,106
God be with you.

1875
02:46:45,054 --> 02:46:46,612
- Mother. - Yes?

1876
02:46:46,856 --> 02:46:50,053
Would it help if we sang about our favorite things?

1877
02:46:50,293 --> 02:46:53,285
No, darling. This is one time it would not help.

1878
02:46:53,563 --> 02:46:56,760
You must be very quiet. Hold tight to me.

1879
02:49:11,434 --> 02:49:12,662
Let's try the roof.

1880
02:50:08,925 --> 02:50:11,155
Rolfe, please.

1881
02:50:16,265 --> 02:50:17,755
No, wait.

1882
02:50:27,577 --> 02:50:28,908
Maria.

1883
02:50:29,979 --> 02:50:31,412
Children.

1884
02:50:35,451 --> 02:50:38,477
It's you we want, not them.

1885
02:50:38,854 --> 02:50:40,583
Put that down.

1886
02:50:41,657 --> 02:50:44,956
Not another move, or I'll shoot.

1887
02:50:46,662 --> 02:50:48,687
You're only a boy.

1888
02:50:51,701 --> 02:50:55,364
- You don't really belong to them. - Stay where you are.

1889
02:50:57,139 --> 02:50:59,130
Come away with us.

1890
02:51:00,376 --> 02:51:01,536
Before it's too late.

1891
02:51:02,144 --> 02:51:04,476
Not another step. I'll kill you.

1892
02:51:06,782 --> 02:51:10,115
- You give that to me, Rolfe. - Did you hear me?

1893
02:51:11,120 --> 02:51:12,678
I'll kill you.

1894
02:51:14,557 --> 02:51:16,024
Rolfe.

1895
02:51:34,410 --> 02:51:35,741
You'll never be one of them.

1896
02:51:38,514 --> 02:51:40,209
Lieutenant!

1897
02:51:40,483 --> 02:51:41,609
They're here!

1898
02:51:41,817 --> 02:51:43,375
They're here, lieutenant!

1899
02:52:24,694 --> 02:52:26,355
Reverend Mother.

1900
02:52:27,630 --> 02:52:29,461
I have sinned.

1901
02:52:30,633 --> 02:52:32,794
I too, Reverend Mother.

1902
02:52:34,437 --> 02:52:36,769
What is this sin, my children?

1903
02:53:57,052 --> 02:53:58,041
[ENGLISH]

